TFilterID.name: TFilterID
TFilterID.description: the identification number of a filter. 0 indicates an invalid filter-id.

TIPFilterID.name: TIPFilterID
TIPFilterID.description: the identification number of an IP filter.

TMACFilterID.name: TMACFilterID
TMACFilterID.description: the identification number of a MAC filter.

TItemScope.name: TItemScope
TItemScope.description: This textual-convention determines some aspects of an item's behavior regarding creation and use, unused entry garbage collection, and automated promulgation by Element Management System to other systems in the service domain. TItemScope applies to SAP-ingress, SAP-egress, and Network policies, and to IP filters and MAC filters. exclusive: When the scope of an item is defined as exclusive, the item can only be applied once, for example to a single SAP. Attempting to assign the policy to a second SAP is not allowed and will result in an error. If the item is removed from the exclusive SAP, it will become available for assignment to another exclusive SAP. A non-applied exclusive scope policy is a candidate to be removed from the system by a TBD garbage collection command. The system default policies cannot be put into the exclusive scope. An error will be generated if scope exclusive is executed in any policies with a policy-id equal to 1. template: When the scope of an item is defined as template, the item can be applied any number of times. Policies with template scope will not be considered for deletion by a TBD garbage collection command; all items of scope 'template' must be deleted explicitly. The system default policies will always be scope template. An error will occur if a policy-id 1 is attempted to be set to scope exclusive.

TItemMatch.name: TItemMatch
TItemMatch.description: when set to off, the item is not matched. when set to false, packets without the item match the filter. when set to true, packets with the item match the filter.

TEntryIndicator.name: TEntryIndicator
TEntryIndicator.description: Uniquely identifies an entry in a policy or filter table. The value 0 is not a valid entry-id. When used as insertion point the value 0 indicates that entries must be inserted at the very beginning, i.e.before the first entry defined.

TEntryId.name: TEntryId
TEntryId.description: uniquely identifies an entry in a policy or filter table. to facilitate insertion of entries in the tables, we recommend assigning entry IDs by 10s: 10, 20, 30, etc.

TEntryIdOrZero.name: TEntryIdOrZero
TEntryIdOrZero.description: uniquely identifies an entry in a policy or filter table. to facilitate insertion of entries in the tables, we recommend assigning entry IDs by 10s: 10, 20, 30, etc. The value 0, means that the object does not refer to a filter entry at this time.

TFilterAction.name: TFilterAction
TFilterAction.description: action to take on the traffic when no filter entry matches. when set to drop(1), packets matching the filter entry are dropped. when set to forward(2), packets matching the filter entry are forwarded.

TFilterActionOrDefault.name: TFilterActionOrDefault
TFilterActionOrDefault.description: action to take on the traffic when the filter entry matches. when set to drop(1), packets matching the filter entry are dropped. when set to forward(2), packets matching the filter entry are forwarded. when set to default(3), packets matching the filter entry are dropped.

TFilterLogId.name: TFilterLogId
TFilterLogId.description: uniquely identifies an entry in the filter log table. 0 indicates an invalid log-id.

TFilterLogDestination.name: TFilterLogDestination
TFilterLogDestination.description: determines the location where filtered packets are logged.

TTimeRangeState.name: TTimeRangeState
TTimeRangeState.description: The textual convention TTimeRangeState is used to indicate the state of an object that is controlled by a time range. - timeRangeNotApplic: no time range is applicable for this entry. - timeRangeNotActive: A time range is defined but is not active at this moment. - timeRangeActive. A time range is defined, and is activated successfully. - timeRangeActiveDownloadFailed: A time range is defined and is activated, but the corresponding object could not be installed due to resource problems.

TFilterLogSummaryCriterium.name: TFilterLogSummaryCriterium
TFilterLogSummaryCriterium.description: Indicates the field on which log summarisation will be done. - when set to srcAddr, received log packets are summarized based on the src ip/mac-addr - when set to dstAddr, received log packets are summarized based on the dst ip/mac-addr

tIPFilterTable.name: tIPFilterTable
tIPFilterTable.description: Contains a List of all ip filters configured on this system.

tIPFilterEntry.name: tIPFilterEntry
tIPFilterEntry.description: Information about a particular IP Filter entry. Entries are created/deleted by user. Entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tIPFilterId.name: tIPFilterId
tIPFilterId.description: Uniquely identifies an ip filter as configures on this system.

tIPFilterRowStatus.name: tIPFilterRowStatus
tIPFilterRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the tIPFilterTable.

tIPFilterScope.name: tIPFilterScope
tIPFilterScope.description: This object specifies the scope of this filter definition. If defined as exclusive(1), this filter can be instantiated only once as compared to the multiple instances that the filter can have if defined as template(2).

tIPFilterDefaultAction.name: tIPFilterDefaultAction
tIPFilterDefaultAction.description: The action to take for packets that do not match any filter entries.

tIPFilterParamsTable.name: tIPFilterParamsTable
tIPFilterParamsTable.description: A table of all IP filter match entries for all IP filters.

tIPFilterParamsEntry.name: tIPFilterParamsEntry
tIPFilterParamsEntry.description: Information about a particular IP Filter entry. Every IP Filter can have zero or more IP Filter match entries. a filter entry with no match criteria set will match every packet, and the entry action will be taken. Entries are created/deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tIPFilterParamsIndex.name: tIPFilterParamsIndex
tIPFilterParamsIndex.description: This is the secondary index for the entry. Every ip filter can have multiple entries, therefore every ip filter entry is identified by the tIPFilterId and tIPFilterParamsIndex.

tIPFilterParamsRowStatus.name: tIPFilterParamsRowStatus
tIPFilterParamsRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the tIPFilterParamsTable.

tIPFilterParamsLogId.name: tIPFilterParamsLogId
tIPFilterParamsLogId.description: This object specifies the log to use for packets that match this entry. The value zero indicates that logging is disabled.

tIPFilterParamsDescription.name: tIPFilterParamsDescription
tIPFilterParamsDescription.description: User-provided description for this filter entry.

tIPFilterParamsAction.name: tIPFilterParamsAction
tIPFilterParamsAction.description: The action to take for packets that match this filter entry. The value default(3) specifies this entry to inherit the behavior defined as the default for the filter.

tIPFilterParamsForwardNH.name: tIPFilterParamsForwardNH
tIPFilterParamsForwardNH.description: The ip-address of the nexthop to which the packet should be forwarded if it hits this filter entry. The action of this entry should be 'forward' in such a case.

tIPFilterParamsForwardNHIndirect.name: tIPFilterParamsForwardNHIndirect
tIPFilterParamsForwardNHIndirect.description: tIPFilterParamsForwardNHIndirect specifies if the nexthop is directly/ indirectly reachable.

tIPFilterParamsRemarkDSCP.name: tIPFilterParamsRemarkDSCP
tIPFilterParamsRemarkDSCP.description: The DSCP value that should be remarked in case a packet hits this filter entry.

tIPFilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask.name: tIPFilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask
tIPFilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask.description: tIPFilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask specifies the care bits while remarking with the DSCP value.

tIPFilterParamsRemarkDot1p.name: tIPFilterParamsRemarkDot1p
tIPFilterParamsRemarkDot1p.description: tIPFilterParamsRemarkDot1p specifies the Dot1p value that needs to be remarked on the packet if it hits this filter entry.

tIPFilterParamsSourceIpAddr.name: tIPFilterParamsSourceIpAddr
tIPFilterParamsSourceIpAddr.description: IP address to match the source-ip of the packet.

tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask.name: tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask
tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask.description: If different from 0, the object tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask specifies the IP Mask value for this policy IP Filter entry. The mask is ANDed with the received source IP address to match the tIPFilterParamsSourceIpAddr. If the value of tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask is 0, and the value of tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask is non zero then the value of tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask is used as mask. If the value of tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask is non zero, it will be equal to the mask expressed the object tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask. If both tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask and tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask are set to 0, not matching is done on the source Ip address. If a value is specified for this object, then the value of the object tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask will be set to reflect this same mask.

tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpAddr.name: tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpAddr
tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpAddr.description: IP address to match the destination-ip of the packet.

tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask.name: tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask
tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask.description: If different from 0, the object tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask specifies the IP Mask value for this policy IP Filter entry. The mask is ANDed with the received Destination IP address to match the tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpAddr. If the value of tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask is 0, and the value of tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask is non zero then the value of tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask is used as mask. If the value of tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask is non zero, it will be equal to the mask expressed the object tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask. If both tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask and tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask are set to 0, not matching is done on the Destination Ip address. If a value is specified for this object, then the value of the object tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask will be set to reflect this same mask.

tIPFilterParamsProtocol.name: tIPFilterParamsProtocol
tIPFilterParamsProtocol.description: IP protocol to match. set to -1 to disable matching IP protocol. If the protocol is changed the protocol specific parameters are reset. For instance if protocol is changed from TCP to UDP, then the objects tIPFilterParamsTcpSyn and tIPFilterParamsTcpAck will be turned off.

tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue1.name: tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue1
tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue1.description: TCP/UDP port value1. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPFilterParamsSourcePortOperator.

tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue2.name: tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue2
tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue2.description: TCP/UDP port value2. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPFilterParamsSourcePortOperator.

tIPFilterParamsSourcePortOperator.name: tIPFilterParamsSourcePortOperator
tIPFilterParamsSourcePortOperator.description: The operator specifies the manner in which tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue1 and tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue2 are to be used. The value of these latter 2 objects and tIPFilterParamsSourcePortOperator is used as described in TTcpUdpPortOperator.

tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue1.name: tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue1
tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue1.description: TCP/UDP port value1. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPFilterParamsDestPortOperator.

tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue2.name: tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue2
tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue2.description: TCP/UDP port value2. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPFilterParamsDestPortOperator.

tIPFilterParamsDestPortOperator.name: tIPFilterParamsDestPortOperator
tIPFilterParamsDestPortOperator.description: The operator specifies the manner in which tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue1 and tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue2 are to be used. The value of these latter 2 objects and tIPFilterParamsDestPortOperator is used as described in TTcpUdpPortOperator.

tIPFilterParamsDSCP.name: tIPFilterParamsDSCP
tIPFilterParamsDSCP.description: DSCP to be matched on the packet.

tIPFilterParamsFragment.name: tIPFilterParamsFragment
tIPFilterParamsFragment.description: If enabled, this object matches fragmented/unfragmented packets as per the value of the object.

tIPFilterParamsOptionPresent.name: tIPFilterParamsOptionPresent
tIPFilterParamsOptionPresent.description: If enabled, this object matches packets if they have options present or not as per the value of the object.

tIPFilterParamsIpOptionValue.name: tIPFilterParamsIpOptionValue
tIPFilterParamsIpOptionValue.description: The value of the specific ip-option to match.

tIPFilterParamsIpOptionMask.name: tIPFilterParamsIpOptionMask
tIPFilterParamsIpOptionMask.description: Mask is ANDed with the ip-option before being compared to tIPFilterParamsIpOptionValue.

tIPFilterParamsMultipleOption.name: tIPFilterParamsMultipleOption
tIPFilterParamsMultipleOption.description: If enabled, matches multiple options as per the value of the object.

tIPFilterParamsTcpSyn.name: tIPFilterParamsTcpSyn
tIPFilterParamsTcpSyn.description: If Enabled, matches a TCP Syn as per value of the object.

tIPFilterParamsTcpAck.name: tIPFilterParamsTcpAck
tIPFilterParamsTcpAck.description: If Enabled, matches a TCP Ack as per value of the object.

tIPFilterParamsIcmpCode.name: tIPFilterParamsIcmpCode
tIPFilterParamsIcmpCode.description: Icmp code to be matched. tIPFilterParamsIcmpCode complements the object tIPFilterParamsIcmpType. Both of them need to be set to actually enable ICMP matching. The value -1 means Icmp code matching is not enabled.

tIPFilterParamsIcmpType.name: tIPFilterParamsIcmpType
tIPFilterParamsIcmpType.description: Icmp type to be matched. tIPFilterParamsIcmpType complements the object tIPFilterParamsIcmpCode. Both of them need to be set to actually enable ICMP matching. The value -1 means Icmp type matching is not enabled.

tIPFilterParamsCflowdSample.name: tIPFilterParamsCflowdSample
tIPFilterParamsCflowdSample.description: When tIPFilterParamsCflowdSample has a value of 'true', Cflowd sampling and analysis is performed on those packet streams where this filter has been applied. Only packets matching this IP filter entry are subjected to Cflowd sampling and analysis. A Cflowd profile controls the sampling and analysis of data flows through the router.

tIPFilterParamsCflowdIfSample.name: tIPFilterParamsCflowdIfSample
tIPFilterParamsCflowdIfSample.description: When tIPFilterParamsCflowdIfSample has a value of 'true', Cflowd sampling and analysis is performed on those packet streams where this filter has been applied. Only packets matching this IP filter entry are subjected to Cflowd sampling and analysis. A Cflowd profile controls the sampling and analysis of data flows through the router.

tIPFilterParamsForwardNHInterface.name: tIPFilterParamsForwardNHInterface
tIPFilterParamsForwardNHInterface.description: The interface name for the nexthop to which the packet should be forwarded if it hits this filter entry. The action of this entry should be 'forward' in such a case.

tIPFilterParamsIngressHitCount.name: tIPFilterParamsIngressHitCount
tIPFilterParamsIngressHitCount.description: This object indicates the number of times an ingress packet matched this entry.

tIPFilterParamsEgressHitCount.name: tIPFilterParamsEgressHitCount
tIPFilterParamsEgressHitCount.description: This object indicates the number of times an egress packet matched this entry.

tIPFilterParamsLogInstantiated.name: tIPFilterParamsLogInstantiated
tIPFilterParamsLogInstantiated.description: tIPFilterParamsLogInstantiated indicates if the filter log for this filter entry has been instantiated or not.

tIPFilterParamsForwardRedPlcy.name: tIPFilterParamsForwardRedPlcy
tIPFilterParamsForwardRedPlcy.description: tIPFilterParamsForwardRedPlcy specifies the redirect policy to be used to determine the nexthop.

tIPFilterParamsActiveDest.name: tIPFilterParamsActiveDest
tIPFilterParamsActiveDest.description: tIPFilterParamsActiveDest indicates the IP address of the active destination for this IP filter. A value of 0 indicates that there is currently no active destination.

tIPFilterParamsFwdSvcId.name: tIPFilterParamsFwdSvcId
tIPFilterParamsFwdSvcId.description: tIPFilterParamsFwdSvcId indicates the service id of the destination for this IP filter entry. A value of 0 indicates that there is currently no active SAP or SDP destination.

tIPFilterParamsFwdSapPortId.name: tIPFilterParamsFwdSapPortId
tIPFilterParamsFwdSapPortId.description: tIPFilterParamsFwdSapPortId specifies the sap port identity of the destination for this IP filter entry. A value of 0 indicates that there is currently no SAP destination defined. A value different from 0 can only be specified if the value of the tIPFilterParamsAction object of this entry is 'forward'. In addition a non-zero value can only be given if the object tIPFilterParamsFwdSdpBind has a zero value.

tIPFilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal.name: tIPFilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal
tIPFilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal.description: tIPFilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal specifies the sap port encap value of the destination SAP for this IP filter entry. A value different from 0 can only be specified if the value of the tIPFilterParamsAction object of this entry is 'forward'. In addition a non-zero value can only be given if the object tIPFilterParamsFwdSdpBind has a zero value. A value of 0 indicates that either 1) the sap encapsulation value is not specified when tIPFilterParamsFwdSapPortId and tIPFilterParamsFwdSvcId have valid values; or 2) that there is no SAP destination.

tIPFilterParamsFwdSdpBind.name: tIPFilterParamsFwdSdpBind
tIPFilterParamsFwdSdpBind.description: tIPFilterParamsFwdSdpBind specifies the sdp bibd identity of the destination for this IP filter entry. A value of 0 indicates that there is currently no SDP binding defined. A value different from 0 can only be specified if the value of the tIPFilterParamsAction object of this entry is 'forward'. In addition a non-zero value can only be given if the objects tIPFilterParamsFwdSapPortId and tIPFilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal have a zero value.

tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeName.name: tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeName
tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeName.description: tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeName specifies the tmnxTimeRangeEntry to be associated with this filter entry. A value for this object can only be specified during row creation, and cannot be altered lateron. Also, a value is accepted only if the tmnxTimeRangeEntry is defined in the TIMETRA-SCHEDULER-MIB::tmnxTimeRangeTable.tTimeRangeName.

tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeState.name: tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeState
tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeState.description: tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeState indicates whether or not the entry is currently in effect. - timeRangeNotApplic: no time range is applicable for this entry. - timeRangeNotActive: A time range is defined in tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeName, but is not active at this moment. Consequently the filter entry is not installed. - timeRangeActive. A time range is defined in tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeName, and is activated successfully. - timeRangeActiveDownloadFailed: A time range is defined in tIPFilterParamsTimeRangeName, and is activated, but the corresponding filter entry could not be installed due to resource problems.

tIPFilterParamsRedirectURL.name: tIPFilterParamsRedirectURL
tIPFilterParamsRedirectURL.description: The value of tIPFilterParamsRedirectURL specifies the URL to redirect to, when the value of tIPFilterParamsAction is 'httpRedirect'.

tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask.name: tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask
tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask.description: If different from 0, the object tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask specifies the IP Mask value for this policy IP Filter entry. The mask is ANDed with the received Source IP address to match the tIPFilterParamsSourceIpAddr. If the value of tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask is non zero, it will be equal to the mask expressed the object tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask. If both tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask and tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask are set to 0, no matching is done on the Source Ip address. This object should contain consecutive ones and zeros. Both a regular and an inverse mask is allowed (i.e. the sequence of consecutive ones can appear at the front or at the end of the mask). If a regular mask is specified for tIPFilterParamsSrcIpFullMask then the value of tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask will be changed to reflect this value. If an inverse is specified, the value of tIPFilterParamsSourceIpMask will be set to 0.

tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask.name: tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask
tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask.description: If different from 0, the object tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask specifies the IP Mask value for this policy IP Filter entry. The mask is ANDed with the received Destination IP address to match the tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpAddr. If the value of tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask is non zero, it will be equal to the mask expressed the object tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask. If both tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask and tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask are set to 0, no matching is done on the Destination Ip address. This object should contain consecutive ones and zeros. Both a regular and an inverse mask is allowed (i.e. the sequence of consecutive ones can appear at the front or at the end of the mask). If a regular mask is specified for tIPFilterParamsDestIpFullMask then the value of tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask will be changed to reflect this value. If an inverse is specified, the value of tIPFilterParamsDestinationIpMask will be set to 0.

tIPFilterParamsIngrHitByteCount.name: tIPFilterParamsIngrHitByteCount
tIPFilterParamsIngrHitByteCount.description: The value of tIPFilterParamsIngrHitByteCount indicates the number of bytes of all ingress packets that matched this entry.

tIPFilterParamsEgrHitByteCount.name: tIPFilterParamsEgrHitByteCount
tIPFilterParamsEgrHitByteCount.description: The value of tIPFilterParamsEgrHitByteCount indicates the number of bytes of all egress packets that matched this entry.

tMacFilterTable.name: tMacFilterTable
tMacFilterTable.description: Contains a List of all mac filters configured on this system.

tMacFilterEntry.name: tMacFilterEntry
tMacFilterEntry.description: Information about a particular MAC Filter. Entries are created/deleted by user. Entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tMacFilterId.name: tMacFilterId
tMacFilterId.description: Uniquely identifies a mac filter as configures on this system.

tMacFilterRowStatus.name: tMacFilterRowStatus
tMacFilterRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the tMacFilterTable.

tMacFilterScope.name: tMacFilterScope
tMacFilterScope.description: This object specifies the scope of this filter definition. If defined as exclusive(1), this filter can be instantiated only once as compared to the multiple instances that the filter can have if defined as template(2).

tMacFilterDefaultAction.name: tMacFilterDefaultAction
tMacFilterDefaultAction.description: The action to take for packets that do not match any filter entries.

tMacFilterParamsTable.name: tMacFilterParamsTable
tMacFilterParamsTable.description: A table of all MAC filter match entries for all MAC filters.

tMacFilterParamsEntry.name: tMacFilterParamsEntry
tMacFilterParamsEntry.description: Information about a particular MAC Filter entry. Every MAC Filter can have zero or more MAC Filter match entries. a filter entry with no match criteria set will match every packet, and the entry action will be taken. Entries are created/deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tMacFilterParamsIndex.name: tMacFilterParamsIndex
tMacFilterParamsIndex.description: This is the secondary index for the entry. Every mac filter can have multiple entries, therefore every mac filter entry is identified by the tMacFilterId and tMacFilterParamsIndex.

tMacFilterParamsRowStatus.name: tMacFilterParamsRowStatus
tMacFilterParamsRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the tMacFilterParamsTable.

tMacFilterParamsLogId.name: tMacFilterParamsLogId
tMacFilterParamsLogId.description: This object specifies the log to use for packets that match this entry. The value zero indicates that logging is disabled.

tMacFilterParamsDescription.name: tMacFilterParamsDescription
tMacFilterParamsDescription.description: User-provided description for this filter entry.

tMacFilterParamsAction.name: tMacFilterParamsAction
tMacFilterParamsAction.description: The action to take for packets that match this filter entry. The value default(3) specifies this entry to inherit the behavior defined as the default for the filter.

tMacFilterParamsFrameType.name: tMacFilterParamsFrameType
tMacFilterParamsFrameType.description: The type of mac frame for which we are defining this match criteria.

tMacFilterParamsSrcMAC.name: tMacFilterParamsSrcMAC
tMacFilterParamsSrcMAC.description: Source MAC to match for this policy MAC filter entry.

tMacFilterParamsSrcMACMask.name: tMacFilterParamsSrcMACMask
tMacFilterParamsSrcMACMask.description: Source MAC mask value for this policy MAC filter entry. The mask is ANDed with the MAC to match tMacFilterParamsSrcMAC. A zero bit means ignore this bit, do not match. a one bit means match this bit with tMacFilterParamsSrcMAC. Use the value 00-00-00-00-00-00 to disable this filter criteria.

tMacFilterParamsDstMAC.name: tMacFilterParamsDstMAC
tMacFilterParamsDstMAC.description: Destination MAC mask value for this policy MAC filter entry.

tMacFilterParamsDstMACMask.name: tMacFilterParamsDstMACMask
tMacFilterParamsDstMACMask.description: Destination MAC mask value for this policy MAC filter entry. The mask is ANDed with the MAC to match tMacFilterParamsDstMAC. A zero bit means ignore this bit, do not match. a one bit means match this bit with tMacFilterParamsDstMAC. Use the value 00-00-00-00-00-00 to disable this filter criteria.

tMacFilterParamsDot1pValue.name: tMacFilterParamsDot1pValue
tMacFilterParamsDot1pValue.description: IEEE 802.1p priority value for this policy MAC filter entry. Use -1 to disable matching this filter criteria.

tMacFilterParamsDot1pMask.name: tMacFilterParamsDot1pMask
tMacFilterParamsDot1pMask.description: IEEE 802.1p priority mask value for this policy MAC filter entry. Use zero to disable matching, use 7 to match everything.

tMacFilterParamsEtherType.name: tMacFilterParamsEtherType
tMacFilterParamsEtherType.description: Ethertype for this policy MAC filter entry. Use -1 to disable matching by this criteria. This object has no significance if the object tMacFilterParamsFrameType is not set to Ethernet_II.

tMacFilterParamsDsap.name: tMacFilterParamsDsap
tMacFilterParamsDsap.description: MAC DSAP to match for this policy MAC filter entry. This object has no significance if the object tMacFilterParamsFrameType is not set to 802dot2LLC.

tMacFilterParamsDsapMask.name: tMacFilterParamsDsapMask
tMacFilterParamsDsapMask.description: MAC DSAP mask for this policy MAC filter entry. use 0 to disable matching by this criteria. This object has no significance if the object tMacFilterParamsFrameType is not set to 802dot2LLC.

tMacFilterParamsSsap.name: tMacFilterParamsSsap
tMacFilterParamsSsap.description: MAC SSAP to match for this policy MAC filter entry. This object has no significance if the object tMacFilterParamsFrameType is not set to 802dot2LLC.

tMacFilterParamsSsapMask.name: tMacFilterParamsSsapMask
tMacFilterParamsSsapMask.description: MAC SSAP mask for this policy MAC filter entry. use 0 to disable matching by this criteria. This object has no significance if the object tMacFilterParamsFrameType is not set to 802dot2LLC.

tMacFilterParamsSnapPid.name: tMacFilterParamsSnapPid
tMacFilterParamsSnapPid.description: MAC SNAP PID to match for this policy MAC filter entry. use -1 to disable matching by this criteria. This object has no significance if object tMacFilterParamsFrameType is not set to 802dot2SNAP.

tMacFilterParamsSnapOui.name: tMacFilterParamsSnapOui
tMacFilterParamsSnapOui.description: MAC SNAP OUI to match. The values zero(2) and nonZero(3) specify what to match. Matching can be disabled by the use of the value off(1). This object has no significance if the object tMacFilterParamsFrameType is not set to 802dot2SNAP.

tMacFilterParamsIngressHitCount.name: tMacFilterParamsIngressHitCount
tMacFilterParamsIngressHitCount.description: This object indicates the number of times an ingress packet matched this entry.

tMacFilterParamsEgressHitCount.name: tMacFilterParamsEgressHitCount
tMacFilterParamsEgressHitCount.description: This object indicates the number of times an egress packet matched this entry.

tMacFilterParamsLogInstantiated.name: tMacFilterParamsLogInstantiated
tMacFilterParamsLogInstantiated.description: tMacFilterParamsLogInstantiated indicates if the filter log for this filter entry has been instantiated or not.

tMacFilterParamsFwdSvcId.name: tMacFilterParamsFwdSvcId
tMacFilterParamsFwdSvcId.description: tMacFilterParamsFwdSvcId indicates the service id of the destination for this Mac filter entry. A value of 0 indicates that there is currently no active SAP or SDP destination.

tMacFilterParamsFwdSapPortId.name: tMacFilterParamsFwdSapPortId
tMacFilterParamsFwdSapPortId.description: tMacFilterParamsFwdSapPortId specifies the sap port identity of the destination for this Mac filter entry. A value of 0 indicates that there is currently no SAP destination defined. A value different from 0 can only be specified if the tMacFilterParamsFwdSvcId object also has a non-zero value, and if the the value of the tMacFilterParamsAction object of this entry is 'forward'. In addition a non-zero value can only be given if the object tMacFilterParamsFwdSdpBind has a zero value.

tMacFilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal.name: tMacFilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal
tMacFilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal.description: tMacFilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal specifies the sap port encap value of the destination SAP for this Mac filter entry. A value different from 0 can only be specified if the tMacFilterParamsFwdSvcId object also has a non-zero value, the tMacFilterParamsFwdSapPortId object has a non zero value, and if the the value of the tMacFilterParamsAction object of this entry is 'forward'. In addition a non-zero value can only be given if the object tMacFilterParamsFwdSdpBind has a zero value. A value of 0 indicates that either 1) the sap encapsulation value is not specified when tMacFilterParamsFwdSapPortId and tMacFilterParamsFwdSvcId have valid values; or 2) that there is no SAP destination.

tMacFilterParamsFwdSdpBind.name: tMacFilterParamsFwdSdpBind
tMacFilterParamsFwdSdpBind.description: tMacFilterParamsFwdSdpBind specifies the sdp bibd identity of the destination for this Mac filter entry. A value of 0 indicates that there is currently no SDP binding defined. A value different from 0 can only be specified if the tMacFilterParamsFwdSvcId object also has a non-zero value, and if the the value of the tMacFilterParamsAction object of this entry is 'forward'. In addition a non-zero value can only be given if the objects tMacFilterParamsFwdSapPortId and tMacFilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal have a zero value.

tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeName.name: tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeName
tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeName.description: tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeName specifies the tmnxTimeRangeEntry to be associated with this filter entry. A value for this object can only be specified during row creation, and cannot be altered lateron. Also, a value is accepted only if the tmnxTimeRangeEntry is defined in the TIMETRA-SCHEDULER-MIB::tmnxTimeRangeTable.tTimeRangeName.

tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeState.name: tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeState
tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeState.description: tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeState indicates whether or not the entry is currently in effect. - timeRangeNotApplic: no time range is applicable for this entry. - timeRangeNotActive: A time range is defined in tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeName, but is not active at this moment. Consequently the filter entry is not installed. - timeRangeActive. A time range is defined in tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeName, and is activated successfully. - timeRangeActiveDownloadFailed: A time range is defined in tMacFilterParamsTimeRangeName, and is activated, but the corresponding filter entry could not be installed due to resource problems.

tMacFilterParamsRedirectURL.name: tMacFilterParamsRedirectURL
tMacFilterParamsRedirectURL.description: The value of tMacFilterParamsRedirectURL specifies the URL to redirect to, when the value of tMacFilterParamsAction is 'httpRedirect'.

tMacFilterParamsIngrHitByteCount.name: tMacFilterParamsIngrHitByteCount
tMacFilterParamsIngrHitByteCount.description: The value of tMacFilterParamsIngrHitByteCount indicates the number of bytes of all ingress packets that matched this entry.

tMacFilterParamsEgrHitByteCount.name: tMacFilterParamsEgrHitByteCount
tMacFilterParamsEgrHitByteCount.description: The value of tMacFilterParamsEgrHitByteCount indicates the number of bytes of all egress packets that matched this entry.

tFilterLogTable.name: tFilterLogTable
tFilterLogTable.description: A table of all filter logs.

tFilterLogEntry.name: tFilterLogEntry
tFilterLogEntry.description: Information about a particular Filter Log entry.

tFilterLogId.name: tFilterLogId
tFilterLogId.description: This is the index for the entry. An entry cannot be created with an id of 0.

tFilterLogRowStatus.name: tFilterLogRowStatus
tFilterLogRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the tFilterLogTable.

tFilterLogDestination.name: tFilterLogDestination
tFilterLogDestination.description: This object specifies the destination of the log.

tFilterLogDescription.name: tFilterLogDescription
tFilterLogDescription.description: User-provided description for this filter log entry.

tFilterLogMaxNumEntries.name: tFilterLogMaxNumEntries
tFilterLogMaxNumEntries.description: This object specifies the maximum number of entries that the log (memory or file) can store. If tFilterLogDestination is not 'memory' then tFilterLogMaxNumEntries maintains a value of '0'

tFilterLogSummaryEnabled.name: tFilterLogSummaryEnabled
tFilterLogSummaryEnabled.description: The value of tFilterLogSummaryEnabled specifies whether or not summarization of filter log entries is performed. Summarization is only allowed in case tFilterLogDestination is set to syslog.

tFilterLogSummaryCrit1.name: tFilterLogSummaryCrit1
tFilterLogSummaryCrit1.description: The value of tFilterLogSummaryCrit1 specifies how filter log entries will be summarized. This field is only meaningful if the object tFilterLogSummaryEnabled is set to true.

tFilterLogMaxInstances.name: tFilterLogMaxInstances
tFilterLogMaxInstances.description: tFilterLogMaxInstances maintains the maximum allowed instances of filter logs allowed on the system

tFilterLogInstances.name: tFilterLogInstances
tFilterLogInstances.description: tFilterLogInstances maintains the instances of filter logs presently existing on the system

tFilterLogBindings.name: tFilterLogBindings
tFilterLogBindings.description: tFilterLogBindings maintains the count of the configured filter log bindings presently existing on the system. The bindings get instantiated when the filter is instantiated

tFilterRedirectPolicyTable.name: tFilterRedirectPolicyTable
tFilterRedirectPolicyTable.description: Contains a List of all redirect policies configured on this system.

tFilterRedirectPolicyEntry.name: tFilterRedirectPolicyEntry
tFilterRedirectPolicyEntry.description: Information about a particular redirect policy. Entries are created/deleted by user.

tFilterRedirectPolicy.name: tFilterRedirectPolicy
tFilterRedirectPolicy.description: tFilterRedirectPolicy uniquely identifies each redirect policy configured on this system.

tFilterRPRowStatus.name: tFilterRPRowStatus
tFilterRPRowStatus.description: tFilterRPRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tFilterRedirectPolicyTable.

tFilterRPDescription.name: tFilterRPDescription
tFilterRPDescription.description: User-provided description for this redirect policy is maintained in the object tFilterRPDescription.

tFilterRPAdminState.name: tFilterRPAdminState
tFilterRPAdminState.description: tFilterRPAdminState holds the admin state of the policy. If the admin state is 'outOfService', the tests will not be conducted.

tFilterRPActiveDest.name: tFilterRPActiveDest
tFilterRPActiveDest.description: tFilterRPActiveDest indicates the IP address of the active destination. A value of 0 indicates that there is currently no active destination.

tFilterRedirectDestTable.name: tFilterRedirectDestTable
tFilterRedirectDestTable.description: Contains a List of all redirect destinations configured on this system.

tFilterRedirectDestEntry.name: tFilterRedirectDestEntry
tFilterRedirectDestEntry.description: Information about a particular Redirect destination. Entries are created/deleted by user.

tFilterRedirectDest.name: tFilterRedirectDest
tFilterRedirectDest.description: tFilterRedirectDest holds the IP address of the destination entry.

tFilterRDRowStatus.name: tFilterRDRowStatus
tFilterRDRowStatus.description: tFilterRDRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tFilterRedirectDestTable.

tFilterRDDescription.name: tFilterRDDescription
tFilterRDDescription.description: User-provided description for this destination is maintained in the object tFilterRDDescription.

tFilterRDAdminPriority.name: tFilterRDAdminPriority
tFilterRDAdminPriority.description: tFilterRDAdminPriority holds the configured base priority for the destination.

tFilterRDOperPriority.name: tFilterRDOperPriority
tFilterRDOperPriority.description: tFilterRDAdminPriority maintains the operational value of the priority for this destination. The highest operational priority across multiple destinations is used as the preferred destination. A value of '0' is maintained if the destination if tFilterRDOperState is 'outOfService'.

tFilterRDAdminState.name: tFilterRDAdminState
tFilterRDAdminState.description: tFilterRDAdminState maintains the configured state of the destination. If the admin state is 'outOfService', the tests for this destination will not be conducted.

tFilterRDOperState.name: tFilterRDOperState
tFilterRDOperState.description: The value of tFilterRDOperState indicates the operational state of the destination.

tFilterRedirectSNMPTestTable.name: tFilterRedirectSNMPTestTable
tFilterRedirectSNMPTestTable.description: Contains a List of all redirect SNMP tests configured on this system.

tFilterRedirectSNMPTestEntry.name: tFilterRedirectSNMPTestEntry
tFilterRedirectSNMPTestEntry.description: Information about a specific SNMP test configured for a destination. Entries are created/deleted by user.

tFilterRedirectSNMPTest.name: tFilterRedirectSNMPTest
tFilterRedirectSNMPTest.description: tFilterRedirectSNMPTest specifies the name of the SNMP test.

tFilterRSTRowStatus.name: tFilterRSTRowStatus
tFilterRSTRowStatus.description: tFilterRSTRowStatus allows tests to be created and deleted in the tFilterRedirectSNMPTestTable.

tFilterRSTOID.name: tFilterRSTOID
tFilterRSTOID.description: tFilterRSTOID stores the OID of the object to be fetched from the destination.

tFilterRSTCommunity.name: tFilterRSTCommunity
tFilterRSTCommunity.description: The value of tFilterRSTCommunity is the SNMPv1 or SNMPv2c Community String or the SNMPv3 Context Name used to conduct this SNMP test as described in RFC2571 and RFC2737. When the value of tFilterRSTSNMPVersion is 'snmpv1' or 'snmpv2c' this object represents a community string. When the value of tFilterRSTSNMPVersion is 'snmpv3' this object represents a SNMPv3 context name.

tFilterRSTSNMPVersion.name: tFilterRSTSNMPVersion
tFilterRSTSNMPVersion.description: tFilterRSTSNMPVersion specifies the SNMP PDU format to be used while conducting the test.

tFilterRSTInterval.name: tFilterRSTInterval
tFilterRSTInterval.description: The value of tFilterRSTInterval specifies the amount of time in seconds between consecutive requests sent to the far end host.

tFilterRSTTimeout.name: tFilterRSTTimeout
tFilterRSTTimeout.description: The value of tFilterRSTTimeout specifies the amount of time in seconds that is allowed for receiving a response from the far end host. If a reply is not received within this time the far end host is considered unresponsive.

tFilterRSTDropCount.name: tFilterRSTDropCount
tFilterRSTDropCount.description: The value of tFilterRSTDropCount specifies the number of consecutive requests that must fail for the destination to declared unreachable.

tFilterRSTHoldDown.name: tFilterRSTHoldDown
tFilterRSTHoldDown.description: The value of tFilterRSTHoldDown specifies the amount of time in seconds that the system should be held down if any of the test has marked it unreachable.

tFilterRSTHoldDownRemain.name: tFilterRSTHoldDownRemain
tFilterRSTHoldDownRemain.description: The value of tFilterRSTHoldDownRemain indicates the amount of time in seconds that the system will remain in held down state before being used again.

tFilterRSTLastActionTime.name: tFilterRSTLastActionTime
tFilterRSTLastActionTime.description: tFilterRSTLastActionTime maintains the time stamp when this test received a response for a probe sent out.

tFilterRSTLastOID.name: tFilterRSTLastOID
tFilterRSTLastOID.description: The object tFilterRSTLastOID holds the OID received in the response.

tFilterRSTLastType.name: tFilterRSTLastType
tFilterRSTLastType.description: tFilterRSTLastType maintains the type of the value received. A value of none(0) indicated that no value has been received

tFilterRSTLastIpAddressVal.name: tFilterRSTLastIpAddressVal
tFilterRSTLastIpAddressVal.description: The value tFilterRSTLastType is 'ipAddress'. Although this seems to be unfriendly for IPv6, we have to recognize that there are a number of older MIBs that do contain an IPv4 format address, known as IpAddress. IPv6 addresses are represented using TAddress or InetAddress, and so the underlying datatype is OCTET STRING, and their value would be stored in the tFilterRSTLastOctetStringVal column.

tFilterRSTLastAction.name: tFilterRSTLastAction
tFilterRSTLastAction.description: tFilterRSTLastAction maintains impact that the last test probe made on the operational status of the destination as maintained in tFilterRDOperState. If the last action was 'disable', the destination may not be used for tFilterRSTHoldDown seconds.

tFilterRSTLastPrioChange.name: tFilterRSTLastPrioChange
tFilterRSTLastPrioChange.description: If the last action on the operational state of the destination i.e. tFilterRSTLastAction is 'enable', tFilterRSTLastPrioChange maintains the impact that the last test probe made on the operational priority of the destination. In other cases, this object has no significance and hence should be holding the value '0'.

tFilterRSTNextRespIndex.name: tFilterRSTNextRespIndex
tFilterRSTNextRespIndex.description: The value of tFilterRSTNextRespIndex indicates the next response index to be used while creating a row in the tFilterRedirectSNMPRespTable. The value of '-1' means that the maximum number of return values for this OID are already configured.

tFilterRedirectSNMPRespTable.name: tFilterRedirectSNMPRespTable
tFilterRedirectSNMPRespTable.description: Each row in this table holds the effect of the test on the destination for a specific return value.

tFilterRedirectSNMPRespEntry.name: tFilterRedirectSNMPRespEntry
tFilterRedirectSNMPRespEntry.description: Information about action to be taken for a specific destination when a specific response is received.

tFilterRSTRespId.name: tFilterRSTRespId
tFilterRSTRespId.description: tFilterRSTRespId holds the response value received from the destination.

tFilterRSTRespRowStatus.name: tFilterRSTRespRowStatus
tFilterRSTRespRowStatus.description: This object allows response strings to be specified for a specific test and the change it will cause to the priority of the destination.

tFilterRSTRespAction.name: tFilterRSTRespAction
tFilterRSTRespAction.description: tFilterRSTRespAction specifies the type of change that should be made to the destination priority tFilterRDOperPriority, if the return value is same as tFilterRSTRespId.

tFilterRSTRespPrioChange.name: tFilterRSTRespPrioChange
tFilterRSTRespPrioChange.description: tFilterRSTRespPrioChange specifies the amount of change to be made to the priority of the destination if the tFilterRSTRespAction is either 'increase' or 'decrease'.

tFilterRSTRespOID.name: tFilterRSTRespOID
tFilterRSTRespOID.description: The object tFilterRSTRespOID holds the OID to be received in the response.

tFilterRSTRespType.name: tFilterRSTRespType
tFilterRSTRespType.description: tFilterRSTRespType maintains the type of the value to be received.

tFilterRSTIpAddressVal.name: tFilterRSTIpAddressVal
tFilterRSTIpAddressVal.description: The value tFilterRSTRespType is 'ipAddress'. Although this seems to be unfriendly for IPv6, we have to recognize that there are a number of older MIBs that do contain an IPv4 format address, known as IpAddress. IPv6 addresses are represented using TAddress or InetAddress, and so the underlying datatype is OCTET STRING, and their value would be stored in the tFilterRSTOctetStringVal column.

tFilterRedirectURLTestTable.name: tFilterRedirectURLTestTable
tFilterRedirectURLTestTable.description: Contains a List of all redirect snmp tests configured on this system.

tFilterRedirectURLTestEntry.name: tFilterRedirectURLTestEntry
tFilterRedirectURLTestEntry.description: Information about a specific URL test configured for a destination. Entries are created/deleted by user. Entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tFilterRedirectURLTest.name: tFilterRedirectURLTest
tFilterRedirectURLTest.description: tFilterRedirectURLTest holds the name of the URL test.

tFilterRUTRowStatus.name: tFilterRUTRowStatus
tFilterRUTRowStatus.description: tFilterRUTRowStatus allows tests to be created and deleted in the tFilterRedirectURLTestTable.

tFilterRUTURL.name: tFilterRUTURL
tFilterRUTURL.description: This object holds the URL to be probed.

tFilterRUTHTTPVersion.name: tFilterRUTHTTPVersion
tFilterRUTHTTPVersion.description: The HTTP Version to be used while performing the URL test. The system by default uses HTTP Version 1.1 until explicitly specified.

tFilterRUTInterval.name: tFilterRUTInterval
tFilterRUTInterval.description: The value of tFilterRUTInterval specifies the amount of time in seconds between consecutive requests sent to the far end host.

tFilterRUTTimeout.name: tFilterRUTTimeout
tFilterRUTTimeout.description: The value of tFilterRUTTimeout specifies the amount of time in seconds that is allowed for receiving a response from the far end host. If a reply is not received within this time the far end host is considered unresponsive.

tFilterRUTDropCount.name: tFilterRUTDropCount
tFilterRUTDropCount.description: The value of tFilterRUTDropCount specifies the number of consecutive requests that must fail for the destination to declared unreachable.

tFilterRUTHoldDown.name: tFilterRUTHoldDown
tFilterRUTHoldDown.description: The value of tFilterRUTHoldDown specifies the amount of time in seconds that the system should be held down if any of the test has marked it unreachable.

tFilterRUTHoldDownRemain.name: tFilterRUTHoldDownRemain
tFilterRUTHoldDownRemain.description: The value of tFilterRUTHoldDownRemain indicates the amount of time in seconds that the system will remain in held down state before being used again.

tFilterRUTLastActionTime.name: tFilterRUTLastActionTime
tFilterRUTLastActionTime.description: tFilterRUTLastActionTime maintains the time stamp when this test received a response for a probe sent out.

tFilterRUTLastRetCode.name: tFilterRUTLastRetCode
tFilterRUTLastRetCode.description: tFilterRUTLastRetCode holds the return code received in the last response.

tFilterRUTLastAction.name: tFilterRUTLastAction
tFilterRUTLastAction.description: tFilterRUTLastAction maintains impact that the last test probe made on the operational status of the destination as maintained in tFilterRDOperState. If the last action was 'disable', the destination may not be used for tFilterRUTHoldDown seconds.

tFilterRUTLastPrioChange.name: tFilterRUTLastPrioChange
tFilterRUTLastPrioChange.description: If the last action on the operational state of the destination i.e. tFilterRUTLastAction is 'enable', tFilterRUTLastPrioChange maintains the impact that the last test probe made on the operational priority of the destination. In other cases, this object has no significance and hence should be holding the value '0'.

tFilterRedirectURLRespTable.name: tFilterRedirectURLRespTable
tFilterRedirectURLRespTable.description: Each row in this table holds the effect of the test on the destination for a range of return values.

tFilterRedirectURLRespEntry.name: tFilterRedirectURLRespEntry
tFilterRedirectURLRespEntry.description: Information about action to be taken for a specific destination when a return value within the range specified between tFilterRedirectURLLowRespCode and tFilterRedirectURLHighRespCode is received.

tFilterRedirectURLLowRespCode.name: tFilterRedirectURLLowRespCode
tFilterRedirectURLLowRespCode.description: tFilterRedirectURLLowRespCode specifies the lower return code of the range specified by this entry.

tFilterRedirectURLHighRespCode.name: tFilterRedirectURLHighRespCode
tFilterRedirectURLHighRespCode.description: tFilterRedirectURLHighRespCode specifies the higher return code of the range specified by this entry.

tFilterRUTRespRowStatus.name: tFilterRUTRespRowStatus
tFilterRUTRespRowStatus.description: tFilterRUTRespRowStatus allows the mapping of a range of return codes returned from a specific test to the change it will cause to the priority of the destination.

tFilterRUTRespAction.name: tFilterRUTRespAction
tFilterRUTRespAction.description: If the tFilterRUTRespAction is either 'increase' or 'decrease', tFilterRUTRespPrioChange specifies the offset to applied to the destination base priority tFilterRDAdminPriority to compute the tFilterRDOperPriority as a result of this test. If the tFilterRUTRespAction is set to 'disable', on the reception of the specified response, the destination will be deemed unusable and the tFilterRDOperPriority will be reset to '0'.

tFilterRUTRespPrioChange.name: tFilterRUTRespPrioChange
tFilterRUTRespPrioChange.description: tFilterRUTRespPrioChange specifies the amount of change to be made to the priority of the destination if the tFilterRUTRespAction is either 'increase' or 'decrease'.

tFilterRedirectPingTestTable.name: tFilterRedirectPingTestTable
tFilterRedirectPingTestTable.description: Contains a List of all redirect Ping tests configured on this system.

tFilterRedirectPingTestEntry.name: tFilterRedirectPingTestEntry
tFilterRedirectPingTestEntry.description: Information about a specific Ping test configured for a destination. Entries are created/deleted by user. Entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tFilterRPTRowStatus.name: tFilterRPTRowStatus
tFilterRPTRowStatus.description: This object allows tests to be created and deleted in the tFilterRedirectPingTestTable.

tFilterRPTInterval.name: tFilterRPTInterval
tFilterRPTInterval.description: The value of tFilterRPTInterval specifies the amount of time in seconds between consecutive requests sent to the far end host.

tFilterRPTTimeout.name: tFilterRPTTimeout
tFilterRPTTimeout.description: The value of tFilterRPTTimeout specifies the amount of time in seconds that is allowed for receiving a response from the far end host. If a reply is not received within this time the far end host is considered unresponsive.

tFilterRPTDropCount.name: tFilterRPTDropCount
tFilterRPTDropCount.description: The value of tFilterRPTDropCount specifies the number of consecutive requests that must fail for the destination to declared unreachable.

tFilterRPTHoldDown.name: tFilterRPTHoldDown
tFilterRPTHoldDown.description: The value of tFilterRPTHoldDown specifies the amount of time in seconds that the system should be held down if any of the test has marked it unreachable.

tFilterRPTHoldDownRemain.name: tFilterRPTHoldDownRemain
tFilterRPTHoldDownRemain.description: The value of tFilterRPTHoldDownRemain indicates the amount of time in seconds that the system will remain in held down state before being used again.

tFilterRPTLastActionTime.name: tFilterRPTLastActionTime
tFilterRPTLastActionTime.description: tFilterRPTLastActionTime maintains the time stamp when this test received a response for a probe sent out.

tFilterRPTLastAction.name: tFilterRPTLastAction
tFilterRPTLastAction.description: tFilterRPTLastAction maintains impact that the last test probe made on the operational status of the destination as maintained in tFilterRDOperState. If the last action was 'disable', the destination may not be used for tFilterRPTHoldDown seconds.

tAutoIPFilterEntryTable.name: tAutoIPFilterEntryTable
tAutoIPFilterEntryTable.description: Defines the Alcatel 7x50 SR series automatic IP filters for providing, via SNMP, the capability of gathering information regarding the same. tAutoIPFilterEntryTable holds a list of all automatic filter entries being used for filtering. This table is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tAutoIPFilterEntry.name: tAutoIPFilterEntry
tAutoIPFilterEntry.description: Defines an entry in the tAutoIPFilterEntryTable. Entries are created and deleted in this table by the system. Each entry provides information about a single active automatic filter entry. This entry is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tAutoIPFilterId.name: tAutoIPFilterId
tAutoIPFilterId.description: tAutoIPFilterId serves as a primary index and uniquely identifies an application point such as a routed interface or a SAP. This object is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tAutoIPFilterEntrySourceIpAddr.name: tAutoIPFilterEntrySourceIpAddr
tAutoIPFilterEntrySourceIpAddr.description: tAutoIPFilterEntrySourceIpAddr specifies the source ip-address and also serves as the secondary index to this table. This object is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tAutoIPFilterEntrySourceIpMask.name: tAutoIPFilterEntrySourceIpMask
tAutoIPFilterEntrySourceIpMask.description: The value of tAutoIPFilterEntrySourceIpMask indicates the number of bits to be matched in the source ip-address. This object is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tFilterDomainLastChanged.name: tFilterDomainLastChanged
tFilterDomainLastChanged.description: timestamp of last change to tFilterObjects.

tIPv6FilterTable.name: tIPv6FilterTable
tIPv6FilterTable.description: Contains a List of all IPv6 filters configured on this system.

tIPv6FilterEntry.name: tIPv6FilterEntry
tIPv6FilterEntry.description: Information about a particular IPv6 Filter entry. Entries are created/deleted by user. Entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tIPv6FilterId.name: tIPv6FilterId
tIPv6FilterId.description: The value of the object tIPv6FilterId uniquely identifies a IPv6 filter on this system.

tIPv6FilterRowStatus.name: tIPv6FilterRowStatus
tIPv6FilterRowStatus.description: The value of the object tIPv6FilterRowStatus specifies the status of the IPv6 filter. The object allows entries to be created and deleted in the tIPv6FilterTable.

tIPv6FilterScope.name: tIPv6FilterScope
tIPv6FilterScope.description: The value of the object tIPv6FilterScope specifies the scope of this filter definition. If defined as exclusive(1), this filter can be instantiated only once as compared to the multiple instances that the filter can have if defined as template(2).

tIPv6FilterDescription.name: tIPv6FilterDescription
tIPv6FilterDescription.description: The value of the object tIPv6FilterDescription specifies a user-provided description for this filter.

tIPv6FilterDefaultAction.name: tIPv6FilterDefaultAction
tIPv6FilterDefaultAction.description: The value of the object tIPv6FilterDefaultAction specifies the action to be taken for packets that do not match any of the filter entries.

tIPv6FilterParamsTable.name: tIPv6FilterParamsTable
tIPv6FilterParamsTable.description: A table of all IPv6 filter match entries for all IPv6 filters.

tIPv6FilterParamsEntry.name: tIPv6FilterParamsEntry
tIPv6FilterParamsEntry.description: Information about a particular IPv6 Filter entry. Every IPv6 Filter can have zero or more IPv6 Filter match entries. a filter entry with no match criteria set will match every packet, and the entry action will be taken. Entries are created/deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tIPv6FilterParamsIndex.name: tIPv6FilterParamsIndex
tIPv6FilterParamsIndex.description: This is the secondary index for the entry. Every IPv6 filter can have multiple entries, therefore every IPv6 filter entry is identified by the tIPv6FilterId and tIPv6FilterParamsIndex.

tIPv6FilterParamsRowStatus.name: tIPv6FilterParamsRowStatus
tIPv6FilterParamsRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the tIPv6FilterParamsTable.

tIPv6FilterParamsLogId.name: tIPv6FilterParamsLogId
tIPv6FilterParamsLogId.description: This object specifies the log to use for packets that match this entry. The value zero indicates that logging is disabled.

tIPv6FilterParamsDescription.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDescription
tIPv6FilterParamsDescription.description: User-provided description for this filter entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsAction.name: tIPv6FilterParamsAction
tIPv6FilterParamsAction.description: The action to take for packets that match this filter entry. The value default(3) specifies this entry to inherit the behavior defined as the default for the filter.

tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNH.name: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNH
tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNH.description: The ipv6-address of the nexthop to which the packet should be forwarded if it hits this filter entry. The action of this entry should be 'forward' in such a case.

tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHIndirect.name: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHIndirect
tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHIndirect.description: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHIndirect specifies if the nexthop is directly or indirectly reachable.

tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCP.name: tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCP
tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCP.description: The DSCP value that should be remarked in case a packet hits this filter entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask.name: tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask
tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask.description: tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask specifies the care bits while remarking with the DSCP value.

tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDot1p.name: tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDot1p
tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDot1p.description: tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDot1p specifies the Dot1p value that needs to be remarked on the packet if it hits this filter entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpAddr.name: tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpAddr
tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpAddr.description: IPv6 address to match the source-ip of the packet.

tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpMask.name: tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpMask
tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpMask.description: The IPv6 Mask value for this policy IPv6 Filter entry. The mask is ANDed with the IPv6 to match the tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpAddr.

tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpAddr.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpAddr
tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpAddr.description: IPv6 address to match the destination-ip of the packet.

tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpMask.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpMask
tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpMask.description: The IPv6 Mask value for this policy IPv6 Filter entry. The mask is ANDed with the IPv6 to match the tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpAddr.

tIPv6FilterParamsNextHeader.name: tIPv6FilterParamsNextHeader
tIPv6FilterParamsNextHeader.description: IPv6 next header to match. set to -1 to disable matching IPv6 next header. If the next header is changed the next header specific parameters are reset. For instance if next header is changed from TCP to UDP, then the objects tIPv6FilterParamsTcpSyn and tIPv6FilterParamsTcpAck will be turned off. Because the match criteria only pertains to the last next-header, the following values are not accepted: 0, 43, 44, 50, 51, and 60.

tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue1.name: tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue1
tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue1.description: TCP/UDP port value1. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortOperator.

tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue2.name: tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue2
tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue2.description: TCP/UDP port value2. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortOperator.

tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortOperator.name: tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortOperator
tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortOperator.description: The operator specifies the manner in which tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue1 and tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue2 are to be used.

tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue1.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue1
tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue1.description: TCP/UDP port value1. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortOperator.

tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue2.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue2

tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortOperator.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortOperator
tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortOperator.description: The operator specifies the manner in which tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue1 and tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue2 are to be used.

tIPv6FilterParamsDSCP.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDSCP
tIPv6FilterParamsDSCP.description: DSCP to be matched on the packet.

tIPv6FilterParamsTcpSyn.name: tIPv6FilterParamsTcpSyn
tIPv6FilterParamsTcpSyn.description: If Enabled, matches a TCP Syn as per value of the object.

tIPv6FilterParamsTcpAck.name: tIPv6FilterParamsTcpAck
tIPv6FilterParamsTcpAck.description: If Enabled, matches a TCP Ack as per value of the object.

tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpCode.name: tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpCode
tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpCode.description: Icmp code to be matched. tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpCode complements the object tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpType. Both of them need to be set to actually enable ICMP matching. The value -1 means Icmp code matching is not enabled.

tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpType.name: tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpType
tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpType.description: Icmp type to be matched. tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpType complements the object tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpCode. Both of them need to be set to actually enable ICMP matching. The value -1 means Icmp type matching is not enabled.

tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdSample.name: tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdSample
tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdSample.description: When tIPFilterParamsCflowdSample has a value of 'true', Cflowd sampling and analysis is performed on those packet streams where this filter has been applied. Only packets matching this IPv6 filter entry are subjected to Cflowd sampling and analysis. A Cflowd profile controls the sampling and analysis of data flows through the router.

tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdIfSample.name: tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdIfSample
tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdIfSample.description: When tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdIfSample has a value of 'true', Cflowd sampling and analysis is performed on those packet streams where this filter has been applied. Only packets matching this IPv6 filter entry are subjected to Cflowd sampling and analysis. A Cflowd profile controls the sampling and analysis of data flows through the router.

tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHInterface.name: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHInterface
tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHInterface.description: The interface name for the nexthop to which the packet should be forwarded if it hits this filter entry. The action of this entry should be 'forward' in such a case.

tIPv6FilterParamsIngressHitCount.name: tIPv6FilterParamsIngressHitCount
tIPv6FilterParamsIngressHitCount.description: This object indicates the number of times an ingress packet matched this entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsEgressHitCount.name: tIPv6FilterParamsEgressHitCount
tIPv6FilterParamsEgressHitCount.description: This object indicates the number of times an egress packet matched this entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsLogInstantiated.name: tIPv6FilterParamsLogInstantiated
tIPv6FilterParamsLogInstantiated.description: tIPv6FilterParamsLogInstantiated indicates if the filter log for this filter entry has been instantiated or not.

tIPv6FilterParamsForwardRedPlcy.name: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardRedPlcy
tIPv6FilterParamsForwardRedPlcy.description: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardRedPlcy specifies the redirect policy to be used to determine the nexthop.

tIPv6FilterParamsActiveDest.name: tIPv6FilterParamsActiveDest
tIPv6FilterParamsActiveDest.description: tIPv6FilterParamsActiveDest indicates the IPv6 address of the active destination for this IPv6 filter. A value of 0 indicates that there is currently no active destination.

tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName.name: tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName
tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName.description: tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName specifies the tmnxTimeRangeEntry to be associated with this filter entry. A value for this object can only be specified during row creation, and cannot be altered lateron. Also, a value is accepted only if the tmnxTimeRangeEntry is defined in the TIMETRA-SCHEDULER-MIB::tmnxTimeRangeTable.tTimeRangeName.

tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeState.name: tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeState
tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeState.description: tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeState indicates whether or not the entry is currently in effect. - timeRangeNotApplic: no time range is applicable for this entry. - timeRangeNotActive: A time range is defined in tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName, but is not active at this moment. Consequently the filter entry is not installed. - timeRangeActive. A time range is defined in tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName, and is activated successfully. - timeRangeActiveDownloadFailed: A time range is defined in tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName, and is activated, but the corresponding filter entry could not be installed due to resource problems.

tIPv6FilterParamsIngrHitByteCount.name: tIPv6FilterParamsIngrHitByteCount
tIPv6FilterParamsIngrHitByteCount.description: The value of tIPv6FilterParamsIngrHitByteCount indicates the number of bytes of all ingress packets that matched this entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsEgrHitByteCount.name: tIPv6FilterParamsEgrHitByteCount
tIPv6FilterParamsEgrHitByteCount.description: This tIPv6FilterParamsEgrHitByteCount indicates the number of bytes of all egress packets that matched this entry.

tFilterPBRDropReason.name: tFilterPBRDropReason
tFilterPBRDropReason.description: Used by tIPFilterPBRPacketsDrop to report the failure reason code.

tFilterParmRow.name: tFilterParmRow
tFilterParmRow.description: The value of the object tFilterParmRow indicates the OID of the row status of the applicable filter parameter table. This can be a row from either one of the following tables: - tIPFilterParamsTable; - tMacFilterParamsTable; or - tIPv6FilterParamsTable

tFilterAlarmDescription.name: tFilterAlarmDescription
tFilterAlarmDescription.description: The value of the object tFilterAlarmDescription is a printable character string which contains information about the cause of the problem.

tIPFilterPBRPacketsDrop.name: tIPFilterPBRPacketsDrop
tIPFilterPBRPacketsDrop.description: The tIPFilterPBRPacketsDrop event is generated either when the configuration of a forwarding action refers to an invalid/unconfigured next-hop or if the active interface goes down operationally in the process of active filtering.

tFilterEntryActivationFailed.name: tFilterEntryActivationFailed
tFilterEntryActivationFailed.description: The tFilterEntryActivationFailed event can only be generated for entries that are controlled by a tmnxTimeRangeEntry. If the tmnxTimeRangeEntry becomes active the indicated entry must be installed. The event is generated when this installation failed because of resource problems.

tFilterEntryActivationRestored.name: tFilterEntryActivationRestored
tFilterEntryActivationRestored.description: The tFilterEntryActivationRestored event can only be generated for entries that are controlled by a tmnxTimeRangeEntry. If the tmnxTimeRangeEntry becomes active the indicated entry must be installed. The event tFilterEntryActivationFailed is generated when this installation originally failed because of resources problems, The notification tFilterEntryActivationRestored is sent when either the time range associated with the filter is no longer active, or when the filter entry was installed due to the availability of new resources.
